\begin_layout Standard
The kernel density estimation is a way to learn and reproduce some function,
 in particular in gray images to learn the intensity on each point.
 For me have more sense if it is used to learn one class, for example in
 Mnist learn each number.
 With the corresponding estimation we can for example create an image of
 the average number.
